textAfterTable: 12 Songs Biography Born: 23 June 1956 in Baton Rouge, LA Genre: Pop Years Active: '70s, '80s, '90s, '00s, '10s Although best known as a judge on the Fox television vocal competition American Idol, Randy Jackson is also a longtime bassist, producer, and music industry executive. Born Randall Darius Jackson in Baton Rouge, LA, in 1956, Jackson began playing bass around age 13. Early in his career Jackson nabbed work with a variety of jazz, R&B, and soul artists, including stints with fusion violinist Jean-Luc Ponty and drummer Billy Cobham; however, his most high-profile gig was with the rock band Journey,...
